# enclave ggml wasi-nn backend - GGUF language models (llama.cpp) behind the
# standard wasi:nn interface, against wasmtime v45.0.0.
#
# APPLY ORDER: LAST, after wasmtime-onnx-gpu-strict.patch (this diff is based
# on a tree with the other enclave patches applied - both touch
# crates/wasi-nn/Cargo.toml and backend/mod.rs).
#
# What it adds: crates/wasi-nn/src/backend/ggml.rs (a backend that binds the
# system-linked enclave_llama shim - see wasm/llama-shim/), its registration
# in backend/mod.rs + wit.rs FromStr ("ggml" now parses for -S nn-graph), a
# no-dependency `ggml` cargo feature, build.rs link directives driven by
# ELL_LIB_LOCATION (same system-link pattern as ORT_LIB_LOCATION), and the
# serve-startup preload hoist (serve.rs + wasi-nn lib.rs/in_memory.rs, below).
# The ggml backend adds NO crates (pure std + FFI); the Cargo.lock hunk only
# records the other patches' deps (half, sha2).
#
# Model delivery: -S nn-graph=ggml::<dir> preloads <dir>/model.gguf (or the
# single *.gguf) under the DIRECTORY BASENAME; guests load_by_name() it, so
# weights never transit the guest's 32-bit linear memory - model size is
# bounded by the tenant's share, not wasm32. The model loads ONCE per
# process, AT SERVER STARTUP: upstream `wasmtime serve` preloads -S nn-graph
# inside new_store(), i.e. per request store (wasip2 components get a fresh
# store per request), which would pull a multi-GB GGUF into VRAM on every
# request and free it after. This patch hoists the preload to right after
# the listener binds (weights hit VRAM the moment the deployment is up;
# connections arriving during the load queue in the listen backlog) and
# shares the graphs with every store through Arc'd registry clones
# (InMemoryRegistry gains Clone, lib.rs gains preload_registry()). A preload
# failure kills the server at boot, loudly, instead of failing per request.
# Per-request cost is llama-context allocation only. Contract:
# input "tokens" I32 [1,n] -> output "logits" Fp32 [1,n_vocab]; the KV cache
# lives in the execution context (stateful across compute() calls). GGUF
# volumes must also carry tokenizer.json (guest-side tokenization).
#
# GPU: the llama.cpp libs are GGML_BACKEND_DL builds - the cpu/cuda compute
# backends are dlopened MODULES, loaded by the shim's ell_init() from
# ENCLAVE_GGML_BACKEND_DIR. The wasmtime binary therefore carries NO
# DT_NEEDED on libcuda.so.1 (driver libs exist only where the nvidia
# container runtime injects them - never on CPU-flavor nodes). STRICT GPU:
# offload requested (ENCLAVE_GGML_N_GPU_LAYERS != 0) + no ggml GPU device
# loaded = loud load failure, never a silent CPU fallback. The preload
# registry hardcodes ExecutionTarget::Cpu, so the env is ALSO what turns
# offload on for preloaded graphs (the wasm-manager sets -1 per GPU tenant).
#
# Tuning env (host process only): ENCLAVE_GGML_N_CTX (default 8192),
# ENCLAVE_GGML_N_BATCH (512), ENCLAVE_GGML_N_GPU_LAYERS (-1 = offload all),
# ENCLAVE_GGML_BACKEND_DIR (backend-module dir; unset = exe dir + cwd).
#
# Build: cargo build --release --features "wasi-nn,wasmtime-wasi-nn/ggml"
# with ELL_LIB_LOCATION=<dir holding libenclave_llama.so + libllama.so>
# (the enclave-llamacpp toolchain artifact; llamacpp-toolchain.yml builds it).
# CPU-smoked 2026-07-07 on the fully-patched tree (qwen2.5-0.5b q4_k_m,
# ~114 tok/s via the dlopened cpu module; self-deterministic; strict-GPU
# guard + no-backend failure paths exercised). NOTE: greedy token streams
# differ between GGML_NATIVE=ON and =OFF kernel builds (near-tie argmax
# flips) - compare like with like when validating determinism.
